<div
  data-particle_enable="false"
  data-particle-mobile-disabled="false"
  class="elementor-element elementor-element-fb713a0 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child"
  data-id="fb713a0"
  data-element_type="container"
>
  <div
    class="elementor-element elementor-element-b8ac37f elementor-hidden-mobile elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading"
    data-id="b8ac37f"
    data-element_type="widget"
    data-widget_type="heading.default"
  >
    <div class="elementor-widget-container">
      <h2 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">
        Competitive Gaming&nbsp;REQUIREMENTS
      </h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div
    class="elementor-element elementor-element-e7db502 elementor-hidden-desktop elementor-hidden-tablet elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading"
    data-id="e7db502"
    data-element_type="widget"
    data-widget_type="heading.default"
  >
    <div class="elementor-widget-container">
      <h2 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">
        Competitive Gaming<br />REQUIREMENTS
      </h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div
    class="elementor-element elementor-element-c9f3288 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor"
    data-id="c9f3288"
    data-element_type="widget"
    data-widget_type="text-editor.default"
  >
    <div class="elementor-widget-container">
      <p>1. <strong>History of Gaming</strong>. Do the following:</p>
      <ul style="list-style-type: none">
        <li>
          (a) Create a timeline showing how video gaming has evolved since 1958.
          Include at least one significant event from each decade.<br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.museumofplay.org/video-game-history-timeline/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Video Game History Timeline</a
            ></strong
          >
          <br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.pbs.org/kcts/videogamerevolution/history/index.html"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >The Video Game Revolution</a
            ></strong
          ><br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.si.edu/sidedoor/ep-15-worst-video-game-ever?page=1"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >The Worst Video Game Ever</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (b) Identify and define five major video game genres. Provide an
          example for each.<br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://glitchwave.com/games/genre/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Glitchwave Game Genres</a
            > </strong
          ><br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://esportsinsider.com/esports-genres-explained"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Esports Genres Explained: Everything You Need to Know</a
            ></strong
          ><br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.google.com/search?q=pac+man&amp;rlz=1C1UEAD_enUS1110US1110&amp;oq=pac+man&amp;gs_lcrp=EgZjaHJvbWUqBwgAEAAYjwIyBwgAEAAYjwIyDQgBEC4YgwEYsQMYgAQyCggCEC4YsQMYgAQyDQgDEAAYgwEYsQMYgAQyDQgEEAAYgwEYsQMYgAQyCggFEC4YsQMYgAQyCggGEC4YsQMYgAQyCggHEC4YsQMYgAQyDQgIEC4YgwEYsQMYgAQyDQgJEC4YgwEYsQMYgATSAQgxMjgyajBqN6gCALACAA&amp;sourceid=chrome&amp;ie=UTF-8"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Free Games</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (c) Explain the difference between video gaming and esports. Include
          how esports incorporates elements of organized competition such as
          teams, tournaments, rules, coaching, and spectatorship. Provide two
          examples of games that are commonly played casually as video games but
          are also used in organized esports competition.<br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/12HVwGZbzfuvZNJ1fT7Htygk7BgyFnSXF/view?usp=sharing"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Gaming vs. Esports</a
            ></strong
          ><br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://hwb.gov.wales/keeping-safe-online/views-from-the-experts/video-gaming-and-esports-the-differences-and-distinctions-in-detail"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Video gaming and esports: the differences and distinctions in
              detail</a
            ></strong
          ><br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://help.playvs.com/en/articles/5915810-game-title-overview"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >PlayVS Game Title Overview</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (d) Identify and define five major moments in the development of
          esports as an industry since 1990. Include key tournaments,
          technological advances, and organizations that helped shape
          competitive gaming globally. Discuss your findings with your merit
          badge counselor.<br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://whatisesports.xyz/major-milestones-esports-history-timeline/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Major Milestones in Esports History: A Timeline</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div
    class="elementor-element elementor-element-6561f11 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor"
    data-id="6561f11"
    data-element_type="widget"
    data-widget_type="text-editor.default"
  >
    <div class="elementor-widget-container">
      <p>
        2. <strong>Living the Scout Oath and Law Online</strong>. Do the
        following:
      </p>
      <ul style="list-style-type: none">
        <li>
          (a) Define the term “toxicity in gaming.” Describe a real or
          hypothetical example of toxic behavior in online play and outline how
          the situation could be prevented or resolved by applying the Scout
          Oath and Law.<br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://staticctf.ubisoft.com/8aefmxkxpxwl/1wJowtd0nH3HS8gAANwF3i/0d0f9fe2d3f9ac6315e069b109aad640/Good_Game_Playbook_for_Teens_EN.pdf?_gl=1*vf4lep*_gcl_au*NjE3NjcyODU4LjE3NjQ2ODk1Mzg.*_ga*MTI4NzA5MzI1My4xNzY0Njg5NTM4*_ga_C4N5020N2R*czE3NjQ3MDM4NDYkbzIkZzAkdDE3NjQ3MDM4NDYkajYwJGwwJGgw"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Good Game Playbook for Teens</a
            ></strong
          >
          <br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://alltogethernow.org.au/our-work/far-right-extremism/game-changers-resources-guide/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Game Changer Resource Guide</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (b) List five strategies for handling negative online gaming
          experiences. Describe how each strategy reflects a point of the Scout
          Oath or Law.<br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.twoaveragegamers.com/how-to-deal-with-toxic-players-a-gamers-guide-to-staying-sane-online/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >How to Deal with Toxic Players: A Gamer’s Guide to Staying Sane
              Online</a
            ></strong
          >
          <br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.childline.org.uk/info-advice/bullying-abuse-safety/types-bullying/bullying-cyberbullying/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Bullying and Cyberbullying</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (c) Research the Entertainment Software Rating Board (ESRB) rating
          system. Record the ratings of the video games you own and compare them
          to your age group. Explain to your counselor whether you agree with
          the ESRB descriptions.<br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.internetmatters.org/resources/video-games-age-ratings-explained/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Video games age ratings explained</a
            ></strong
          >
          <br /><a
            href="http://www.esrb.org/search/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            ><strong>Search ESRB Game Ratings</strong></a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (d) List five ways to create a positive online gaming environment for
          yourself and others. Demonstrate one of these methods with your troop,
          patrol, or family.<br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.twoaveragegamers.com/the-ultimate-guide-to-non-toxic-gaming-communities/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >The Ultimate Guide to Non-Toxic Gaming Communities</a
            ></strong
          >
          <br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.twoaveragegamers.com/the-ultimate-guide-to-non-toxic-gaming-communities/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >StopBullying.gov – What Kids Can Do</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div
    class="elementor-element elementor-element-e336f48 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor"
    data-id="e336f48"
    data-element_type="widget"
    data-widget_type="text-editor.default"
  >
    <div class="elementor-widget-container">
      <p>3. <strong>Gamer Health and Balance</strong>. Do the following:</p>
      <ul style="list-style-type: none">
        <li>
          (a) Read two credible articles describing positive aspects of video
          gaming and two describing negative aspects. Create a chart showing
          where the articles agree or disagree.
        </li>
        <li>
          Positive aspects <br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.popsci.com/health/video-game-benefits/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >The surprising benefits of video games</a
            ></strong
          ><br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://health.clevelandclinic.org/are-video-games-good-for-you"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Are Video Games Good for You? Your Brain Thinks So</a
            ></strong
          ><br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.ted.com/talks/kris_alexander_how_video_games_can_level_up_the_way_you_learn?referrer=playlist-talks_for_gamers&amp;autoplay=true"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >How Video Games Can Level Up the Way You Learn</a
            ></strong
          ><br /><a
            href="https://www.aoa.org/healthy-eyes/caring-for-your-eyes/welcome-to-blink-land"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            ><strong>Welcome to Blink Land</strong></a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          Negative aspects <br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.kidsvillepeds.com/blog/1290873-how-video-games-affect-kids-behavioral-health-the-hidden-risks/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >How Video Games Affect Kids’ Behavioral Health: The Hidden
              Risks</a
            ></strong
          ><br /><a
            href="https://www.brightpathbh.com/effects-of-video-games-on-teen-mental-health/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            ><strong>Effects Of Video Games On Teen Mental Health</strong></a
          ><br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.sciencejournalforkids.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/screentime-ADHD_Article.pdf"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >What is the link between screen time and ADHD?</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (b) Track the amount of gaming you do each day for two weeks. Record
          and summarize your results.<br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://wordunited.com/free-resources/screen-time-tracker/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Screen Time Tracker</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (c) Track your daily physical activity for the same two weeks. Compare
          your results to the CDC recommendation of one hour of
          moderate-to-vigorous activity per day for youth ages 6–17.<br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.cdc.gov/healthyweight/pdf/physical_activity_diary_cdc.pdf"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >My Physical Activity Diary</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (d) Track your daily sleep for the same two weeks. Compare your
          results to the CDC recommendation of 9–12 hours for ages 6–12 and 8–10
          hours for ages 13–18.<br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://thesleepcharity.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/The-Sleep-Charity-Teens-Sleep-Diary.pdf"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Teen Sleep Diary</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (e) After completing 3b, 3c, and 3d, create a one-week balanced
          schedule that includes healthy sleep, physical activity, and
          agreed-upon gaming time. Follow this schedule and summarize your
          results.<br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.cci.health.wa.gov.au/~/media/CCI/Mental-Health-Professionals/Depression/Depression-Worksheets/Depression-Worksheet---03---Weekly-Activity-Schedule.pdf"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Weekly Activity Schedule</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div
    class="elementor-element elementor-element-ae2da29 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor"
    data-id="ae2da29"
    data-element_type="widget"
    data-widget_type="text-editor.default"
  >
    <div class="elementor-widget-container">
      <p>
        4. <strong>Gamer Safety and Community Connection</strong>. Do the
        following:
      </p>
      <ul style="list-style-type: none">
        <li>
          (a) Explain the benefits and risks of gaming online.<br />
          <strong
            ><a
              href="https://builtin.com/articles/online-gaming-social-benefits"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >The Real Benefits of Video Games</a
            ></strong
          ><br />
          <strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.smartsocial.com/post/negative-effects-video-games"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Negative Effects of Video Games</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (b) Research and list ten ways to stay safe when playing video games
          online.<br />
          <strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.internetmatters.org/issues/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Online safety issues</a
            ></strong
          ><br />
          <strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.dhs.gov/sites/default/files/2024-09/24_09_20_K2P_Gaming-Safety.pdf"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Gaming Safety</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (c) Play one of your favorite games with your parent or guardian for
          at least 30 minutes. Demonstrate how to use privacy and safety
          settings, explain what you enjoy about the game, and let them play for
          part of the session.<br />
          <strong
            ><a
              href="https://internetsafety101.org/objects/Gaming-controls-quick-guide-03-24-2025.pdf"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Online Gaming Safety Settings</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (d) Play an online or local multiplayer game with another Scout,
          friend, or community member in a cooperative or team-based setting.
          The match may be casual or competitive. During play, demonstrate
          positive communication, teamwork, and sportsmanship. Afterward, review
          the experience with your counselor and describe how cooperation and
          communication influenced your team’s performance and overall enjoyment
          of the game.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div
    class="elementor-element elementor-element-0dbd2c0 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor"
    data-id="0dbd2c0"
    data-element_type="widget"
    data-widget_type="text-editor.default"
  >
    <div class="elementor-widget-container">
      <p>
        5. <strong>Technology in Competitive Gaming</strong>. Do the following:
      </p>
      <ul style="list-style-type: none">
        <li>
          (a) Explain the difference between console gaming and PC gaming. List
          the advantages and disadvantages of each.<br />
          <strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.seagate.com/blog/console-vs-pc-gaming/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Console vs. PC Gaming: Which Is Better?</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (b) Play the same game on at least two different platforms. Describe
          the similarities and differences in gameplay and performance.
        </li>
        <li>
          (c) Visit a PC builder website such as PCPartPicker or Micro Center.
          Design your ideal gaming PC and create a parts list that includes:
          central processing unit (CPU), motherboard, random access memory
          (RAM), hard drive, power supply, graphics card, fans, case. Discuss
          your selections with your counselor.<br />
          <strong
            ><a href="https://pcpartpicker.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
              >PCPartPicker</a
            ></strong
          ><br />
          <strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.microcenter.com/site/content/custom-pc-builder.aspx?k=1764714012175"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Micro Center</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div
    class="elementor-element elementor-element-baae49e elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor"
    data-id="baae49e"
    data-element_type="widget"
    data-widget_type="text-editor.default"
  >
    <div class="elementor-widget-container">
      <p>
        6. <strong>Leadership and Service in Competitive Gaming</strong>. Do ONE
        of the following:
      </p>
      <ul style="list-style-type: none">
        <li>
          (a) Teach your troop, patrol, or a group of younger Scouts or family
          members about online gaming safety or digital citizenship.
        </li>
        <li>
          (b) Attend or view a live-streamed esports event online, such as a
          professional tournament, collegiate match, or school-level
          competition. Take notes on how the broadcast team presents the event,
          how players communicate, and how the audience interacts digitally.
          Share with your merit badge counselor what you learned about the
          structure and presentation of online esports competition.
        </li>
        <li>
          (c) Attend an esports tournament, convention, or community event that
          includes a competitive gaming activity or demonstration. Attend with
          another Scout, troop member, or family member. Afterward, share with
          your merit badge counselor what you learned about the atmosphere of
          live esports events and how the experience changed your understanding
          of playing games competitively in front of an audience.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div
    class="elementor-element elementor-element-924ff5d elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor"
    data-id="924ff5d"
    data-element_type="widget"
    data-widget_type="text-editor.default"
  >
    <div class="elementor-widget-container">
      <p>
        <strong
          >7. Exploring Professions in the Competitive Gaming Industry</strong
        >. Do the following:
      </p>
      <ul style="list-style-type: none">
        <li>
          (a) Research two colleges that offer varsity esports programs. Record
          the following information for each: availability and amount of gaming
          scholarships, offered gaming or IT-related degrees, games played by
          the esports team, league or association in which the team competes.<br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.nacesports.org/school-directory"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >NACE School Directory</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (b) Research three gaming-adjacent careers that support or connect to
          the esports industry but are not esports athlete roles. Examples may
          include: game designer or developer, shoutcaster or broadcast
          producer, data analyst or statistician, marketing or event
          coordinator, IT or network support specialist. For each career,
          identify the main responsibilities, education or training
          requirements, and how the role contributes to the success of the
          gaming or esports ecosystem.<br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.flipbookpdf.net/web/site/0f69cbe0b3ab4127778010bc84c0383f86c1f5a5FBP25582848.pdf.html#page/5"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >100 Jobs in Esports</a
            ></strong
          ><br /><strong
            ><a href="https://hitmarker.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
              >Hitmarker</a
            ></strong
          ><br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dY42XJUcBME"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Careers in Esports</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          (c) Visit the “Careers” or “Jobs” page of a major game publisher (such
          as Blizzard, Riot, Epic or Nintendo). Choose three jobs that interest
          you. For each, identify the required education, skills, and
          experience.<br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://careers.blizzard.com/global/en"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Careers at Blizzard Entertainment</a
            ></strong
          ><br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.riotgames.com/en/work-with-us"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Riot Games – Work With Us</a
            ></strong
          ><br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://www.epicgames.com/site/en-US/careers"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Epic Games Careers, Jobs and Employment Opportunity</a
            ></strong
          ><br /><strong
            ><a
              href="https://careers.nintendo.com/?gad_source=1&amp;gad_campaignid=23316994690&amp;gbraid=0AAAAADRjo1BdA9FCGJbrIDtNxQtsooPUJ&amp;gclid=Cj0KCQiAubrJBhCbARIsAHIdxD_uX8GV_9oXW0Bo8pgw4K2Te4_KW0N734Bqtkbv1TKh1Khs3cmL8jEaAlXqEALw_wcB"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              >Careers at Nintendo of America</a
            ></strong
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div
    class="elementor-element elementor-element-83132be elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor"
    data-id="83132be"
    data-element_type="widget"
    data-widget_type="text-editor.default"
  >
